In casserole dish, combine oil, onion, garlic, ginger, curry paste and cayenne pepper. Microwave, covered, on High for 2 to 3 minutes, until onion is softened. Add potatoes, carrots, stock and tomato paste. Microwave, covered, on High for 10 to 14 minutes, stirring once, until vegetables are tender. Add lentils. Microwave, covered, on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until piping hot. Season with salt, if required, and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with cilantro and serve in heated bowls. Top each with a spoonful of yogurt, if desired. Variation: This is a meatless stew but you can add about 1 Â½ cups (375 mL) diced cooked roast lamb, pork or ham along with lentils.